args: That came from the outskirts of the garden!
Hey there, buddy! Gimme a hand?
I got caught in this weird net thingie\nand now I can't move.
Hmm... That's actually a rather clever trap.\nI wonder who set it there?
Uh, maybe help me out before you try\nto reverse engineer it or whatever?
Just toss me my axeâ€”I dropped it\nover there when this thing snagged me.
Er, all right. But how are you going to\ncut through the net when you're also\ncaught inside it?
Just leave it to me! Hyaah!
Nya ha ha! Yeah, when it comes to axes,\nol' Yue is definitely the best around.
I take it your name is Yue, then?\nWell, it's nice to meet you, Yue.\nMy name is {player_name}.
If you don't mind me asking, what are you\ndoing this deep in the woods?
I was chasing a wild boar. It was big\nand fat and meaty and delicious and\njust...so...mmmmrrraaaagh....
Anyway, when it went out to that field to\neat some veggies, I leapt to the attack!
And THAT'S when that stupid trap\ncaught me. Booo!
Perhaps I hid my trap a little\nTOO ingeniously.
Wait, Cleo? YOU made this trap?
I actually had Luca and Ranzal make\nit for me, but I did hang it there.
A wild boar has been making a mess\nof the vegetable garden lately.
Wait. Hold the carrier pigeon.\nI fell into YOUR boar trap?!\nNya ha ha! That's hilarious!
Still, I think you can rest easy now.
Wild boars are easily frightened, so they\nwon't go near places that feel dangerous.
And since I scared it off just now,\nit should leave your veggies alone.
You sure know a lot about boars.
Yeah, my people are all over it\nwhen it comes to critters.
Hunting and traveling is pretty much\nwhat we do!
Oh man, all that fighting with the\nnet has made my tummy rumbly.
Well, perhaps Cleo can do something\nabout that noisy belly of yours.
I would be happy to prepare something.
It was my trap that ensnared you,\nso a meal is the least I can do.
It's also a chance to thank you for\ndriving off that wild boar.
Augh! SO good! The meat is delicious,\nand the bread's so...FLUFFY!
I can't believe you made such a\ntasty meal so quickly, Cleo!
When you cook for a castle of people\nevery day, preparing a meal for one\nis a rather simple task.
Every day... Wait, so if I work at your\ncastle, I can eat like this EVERY day?!
GIVE ME A JOB RIGHT NOOOW!
C'mon, Prince! Hire me! I'll do whatever!
I can fight fiends AND gather food;\nI'm a real double threat!
We'd be happy to have you join us, Yue.
Then just leave your problems to me.
I'll protect you from scary fiends\nAND empty bellies!
